choices.text: Harmony recycled old paper to create handmade notebooks for her friends. The process involved folding five sheets of letter-size paper into thirds, then cutting along the creases to form smaller pieces. These were stacked and stapled together to produce a single notepad. If someone used this pad daily, writing ten notes per day on each page, how long would it last before running out of space?
